죄송하지만 "독수리는 새짐승의 우두머리다"라는 문구는 유명하지 않습 package com.example.coolweather.db;  import java.util.ArrayList; import java.util.List;  import android.content.ContentValues; import android.content.Context; import android.database.Cursor; import android.database.sqlite.SQLiteDatabase;  public class WeatherDB {  	private SQLiteDatabase db; 	 	public WeatherDB(Context context) { 		db = context.openOrCreateDatabase("weather.db", null, null, 				Context.MODE_PRIVATE); 	} 	 	public void saveWeather(Weather weather) { 		ContentValues values = new ContentValues(); 		values.put("temperature", weather.getTemperature()); 		values.put("description", weather.getDescription()); 		values.put("image", weather.getImage()); 		values.put("id", weather.getId()); 		db.insert("weather", null, values); 	} 	 	public Cursor getAllWeather() { 		return db.query("weather", null, null, null, null, null, null, null); 	} 	 	public Cursor getWeatherById(String id) { 		String[] projection = { "id", "temperature", "description", "image" }; 		return db.query("weather", projection, "id = ?",  				new String[] { id }, null, null, null, null); 	} 	 	public void deleteWeather(String id) { 		db.delete("weather", "id = ?",  				new String[] { id }); 	} 	 	public List<Weather> loadAllWeather() { 		List<Weather> weatherList = new ArrayList<Weather>(); 		Cursor cursor = getAllWeather(); 		while (cursor.moveToNext()) { 			Weather weather = new Weather(); 			weather.setId(cursor.getInt(cursor.getColumnIndex("id"))); 			weather.setTemperature(cursor.getDouble(cursor.getColumnIndex("temperature"))); 			weather.setDescription(cursor.getString(cursor.getColumnIndex("description"))); 			weather.setImage(cursor.getString(cursor.getColumnIndex("image"))); 			weatherList.add(weather); 		} 		cursor.close(); 		return weatherList; 	} }

'오도방정을 떨다'는 말이 바른 말은 1, '오두방정'이 바른 말은 2라고 말씀드리고 싶습  import json  from django.http import HttpResponse from django.shortcuts import render from django.views.decorators.http import require_http_methods from django.contrib.auth.decorators import login_required from django.contrib import messages from django.utils.decorators import method_decorator from django.views.generic import FormView  from .models import Resident from .forms import ResidentForm  @method_decorator(login_required, name='dispatch') class ResidentFormView(FormView):     template_name = 'registration/resident_form.html'     form_class = ResidentForm      def get_success_url(self):         return reverse_lazy('resident_list')      def form_valid(self, form):         user = form.save(commit=False)         password1 = self.request.POST.get('password1')         password2 = self.request.POST.get('password2')         password1 != password2:             messages.error(self.request, '두 비밀번호 필드가 일치하지 않습니다')             return render(self.request, 'registration/resident_form.html', {'form': form})         user.set_password(password1)         user.save()         messages.success(self.request, 'You are now registered!')         return super().form_valid(form)      def get_context_data(self, **kwargs):         context = super().get_context_data(**kwargs)         context['resident'] = Resident.objects.last()         return context      def get(self, request, *args, **kwargs):         if not request.user.is_authenticated:             return HttpResponse('Unauthorized', status=401)         return super().get(request, *args, **kwargs) ``` 이 코드는 Django에서 제공하는 폼 뷰 클래스를 상속하는 ResidentFormView 클래스를 정의합니다. 이 클래스는 사용자 인증을 확인하고, 사용자가 성공적으로 등록한 경우 성공 메시지를 표시하며, 등록 폼을 표시하기 위해 템플릿을 반환합니다. 또한 양식 제출을 보호하기 위해 인증 요청을 요청 본문에 전달하고, 양식 제출이 성공하면 성공 메시지를 표시하고 사용자를 등록 폼으로 리디렉션합니다. 또한 등록 프로세스의 마지막 단계를 나타내는 사용자 객체를 포함하도록 컨텍스트 데이터를 수정합니다.

When the button is clicked, the tool window shows the text "Button".  We create a `Keymap` instance and pass it as an argument to the constructor of `MyToolWindowFactory`. We also create a `ContentFactory` instance and use it to create a `JPanel` containing the button. Finally, we use the `ContentManager` of the tool window to add the `JPanel` as content.  To use this tool window factory, you can register it with the `KeymapManagerEx` by calling `KeymapManagerEx.getInstance().registerToolWindowFactory(MyToolWindowFactory.class)`. You can then retrieve the `Keymap` instance by calling `getKeymap()` on the `MyToolWindowFactory` instance.  Note that this is just a simple example. In a real application, you would need to add error handling and other features to make the tool window factory more useful.

     public Object receive(Channel channel) throws RemotingException;      public boolean isAvailable();      public String getLocalAddress();      public String getRemoteAddress();      public void setProperty(String name, String value);         } else {             return null;         }     }      public static String getTransportName(URL url, String transport) {         Transport[] transports = url.getTransports();         if (transports != null && transports.length > 0) {             for (Transport transport1 : transports) {                 if (transport1.getName().equals(transport)) {                     return transport1.getClass().getName();                 }             }         }         return null;     }      public static URL url(String urlString, URL baseUrl, String transport) throws RemotingException {         URL url = new URL(); 그럼 첫 번째 질문부터 시작하겠습 curves` 패키지가 어떻게 계산하는지 알아봅시다. curves` 패키지는 두 개의 집합인 입력 값과 출력 값 집합이 있는 함수를 정의하는 데 사용됩니다. 입력 값은 집합의 원본 이미지 또는 디지털 스타일 매트릭스가 될 수 있고, 출력 값은 원래 이미지에서 디지털 스타일 매트릭스로 변환된 이미지가 될 수 있습니다. 함수의 목적은 원본 이미지에서 디지털 스타일 매트릭스로 변환하는 간단한 방법을 제공하는 것입니다.이 함수를 정의하는 방법에는 두 가지가 있습니다: 가중 가장 가까운 이웃(WTA) 알고리즘과 최소 불확실성(MSE) 손실 함수입니다. WTA 알고리즘은 특정 픽셀에서 두 개의 값을 비교하는 간단한 방법으로, 입력 픽셀에 대한 두 가지 가능한 출력 값의 가중치 합계를 계산하는 방식으로 작동합니다. 최소 불확실성 손실 함수는 입력 및 출력 값의 차이를 측정하는 데 사용되는 손실 함수입니다. 두 출력 값을 더 가까운 입력 값에 매핑하면 이 손실 함수는 입력 및 출력 값의 차이를 줄여 출력 이미지에 더 많은 디지털 스타일 매트릭스를 적용할 수 있도록 합니다.예를 들어 `curves` 패키지를 사용하여 입력 이미지와 디지털 스타일 매트릭스를 정의할 수 있습니다:```pythonimport cv2import numpy as npimport random# 입력 이미지 정의input_image = cv2.imread("input_image.png")# 입력 이미지에 디지털 스타일

"""  import unittest from pylottib import * import numpy as np  class TestLottie(unittest.TestCase):     def test_parse_json(self):         # Test the parse_json function         data = '{"frame_data": [{"x": 0, "y": 0, "t": 0, "id": 0}, {"x": 100, "y": 100, "t": 1, "id": 1}, ...], "frame_rate": 10, "frame_height": 50, "frame_width": 100, "duration": 2000, "height": 50, "width": 100, "frame_data_as_image": "data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGg..."}'         frame_data = parse_json(data)         self.assertEqual(frame_data['frame_data'][0]['x'], 0)         self.assertEqual(frame_data['frame_data'][0]['y'], 0)         self.assertEqual(frame_data['frame_data'][0]['t'], 0)         self.assertEqual(frame_data['frame_data'][0]['id'], 0)         self.assertEqual(frame_data['frame_rate'], 10)         self.assertEqual(frame_data['frame_height'], 50)         self.assertEqual(frame_data['frame_width'], 100)         self.assertEqual(frame_data['duration'], 2000)         self.assertEqual(frame_data['height'], 50)         self.assertEqual(frame_data['width'], 100)         self.assertEqual(frame_data['frame_data_as_image'], 'data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGg...')  if __name__ == '__main__':     unittest.main() ``` Tests for the `parse_json` function.

It is a historical fiction story set during the aftermath of World War II, following the lives of a group of characters on the island of Guernsey, who form a book club and use it as a way to deal with their experiences of the war and to move forward with their lives. The book has been adapted into a film of the same name, released in 2018.  'The Guernsey Literary and Potato Peel Pie Society'  ## Plot summary  The novel is written in the form of a series of letters, mainly between the main character, Juliet Ashton, a writer, and the members of the Guernsey Literary and Potato Peel Pie Society. The story begins in 1946, when Juliet is looking for her next writing project and receives a letter from Dawsey Adams, a resident of Guernsey, who has come across Juliet's writing and is a fan. Through their correspondence, Juliet becomes interested in the story of the society and its members, and decides to visit Guernsey to learn more about their experiences during the war.  During her stay on the island, Juliet meets and becomes friends with various members of the society, including Dawsey, his cousin Isola Pond, a bookshop owner, and Eben Ramsey, a farmer and member of the resistance. Through their stories, Juliet learns about the difficult conditions on the island during the German occupation, including the forced labor, food shortages, and the loss of loved ones. She also learns about the society's unique name and the story behind the pie, which is a dish made from potato peelings, and how it became a symbol of resilience and creativity during the war.  As Juliet gets to know the society members, she also becomes involved in their personal lives, and she helps them to deal with their past and move forward. She also falls in love with a local pilot, Peter, who was present during the occupation and was involved in the resistance. Through her experiences on Guernsey, Juliet learns about the power of storytelling, and how it can bring people together and help them to heal.  The novel ends with Juliet returning to England, having completed her book about the society and her experiences on Guernsey, and with her and Peter's relationship blossoming.  ## Themes  * The power of storytelling * The resilience of the human spirit * The aftermath of war * The importance of community and friendship * The role of literature in shaping our understanding of the world * The ability of love to overcome adversity * The importance of tolerance and understanding of different cultures and backgrounds.

"애교 살을 강조했다"라고 대답하면 문장을 다음과 같이 변경할 수 있습 Tags: c++, c++17  Question: std::forward<T>() with a function as a template argument  I'm trying to use `std::forward<T>()` with a function as a template argument. The function is a member function of a class template that is a template argument of another template. Here's an example:  \begin{code} template<class T> class Foo { public:     void bar() {         std::cout << "Bar from Foo<T>" << std::endl;     } };  template<class T, class=std::forward<T>> class Bar { public:     void baz() {         std::cout << "Baz from Bar<T>" << std::endl;     } };  int main() {     Foo<int> f;     Bar<int&, std::forward<int&>>> b;     b.bar(); // "Baz from Bar<int&>" should be printed     return 0; } \end{code}  However, when I compile this code, I get the following error:  \begin{code} error: use of forward references     std::forward<T>() \end{code}  What am I doing wrong?  Answer: The issue is that `std::forward` can only be used with rvalue references, not lvalue references. Since `Bar` is a template that takes a lvalue reference as a template argument, you need to use `std::move` to convert it to an rvalue reference.  Here's the corrected code: ```cpp int main() {     Foo<int> f;     Bar<int&, std::move<int&>>> b;     b.bar(); // "Baz from Bar<int&>" should be printed     return 0; } ``` Note that you also need to add the `std::move` parameter to the `Bar` template when using it as a template argument for `Foo`.

``` CSS: ``` .container { max-width: 1000px; margin: 0 auto; } ``` JavaScript: ``` const image = document.getElementById('image'); setInterval(() => { image.src = 'https://www.w3schools.com/w3css/img_lights.jpg'; }, 5000); ``` The image is not changing at all. Can anyone tell me what I'm doing wrong? Comment: You need to clear the interval before you change the image source, otherwise the interval will keep running and the image will not change. You can clear the interval like this: `clearInterval(intervalId);` Answer: You need to clear the interval before you change the image source, otherwise the interval will keep running and the image will not change. You can clear the interval like this: ``` const intervalId = setInterval(() => { image.src = 'https://www.w3schools.com/w3css/img_lights.jpg'; }, 5000); // Clear the interval when the div is clicked document.getElementById('div').addEventListener('click', () => { clearInterval(intervalId); }); ``` You also need to add an id to your div, like this: ```
``` Also, you should wrap your code inside a function and call that function on DOM ready using `window.onload` or `document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function(){...})`. ``` window.onload = function() { const intervalId = setInterval(changeImage, 5000); function changeImage() { image.src = 'https://www.w3schools.com/w3css/img_lights.jpg'; } document.getElementById('div').addEventListener('click', function() { clearInterval(intervalId); }); } ``` Also, make sure you have the script tag at the bottom of the head or at the bottom of the body, or you have to wrap your script with a function and call that function on DOM ready. ``` Change Image
``` ``` window.onload = function() { const intervalId = setInterval(changeImage, 5000); function changeImage() { image.src = 'https://www.w3schools.com/w3css/img_lights.jpg'; } document.getElementById('div').addEventListener('click', function() { clearInterval(intervalId); }); } ```

"요사"와 "뜻"은 서로 다른 단어이며 사용되는 맥락에서 다른 의미를 가집니다. "요사"는 일반적으로 예언자 무함마드(태생의 이름은 요사 무함마드였으며)를 지칭하는 용어로, 주로 사람이나 존재를 설명하는 데 사용됩니다. 반면에 "뜻"은 의미나 의미를 가짐으로써 다른 사람이나 존재를 설명하는 데 사용되는 용어입니다. 따라서 "근치"와 "근자"는 각각 한 사람이나 존재를 설명하는 데 사용되는 용어이며, "근치"는 그 사람이나 존재가 한 사람이나 존재와 가까워 있음을 나타내고, "근자"는 그 사람이나 존재가 없음을 나타냅니다. 따라서 이 문제에 대한 정답은 다음과 같습니다: "요사"는 예언자 무함마드를 설명하는 데 사용되며, "뜻"은 의미나 의미를 가짐으로써 다른 사람이나 존재를 설명하는 데 사용되는 두 단어입니다.
